  <static seed="1305" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalFunctions/reduceRationalFunction10.pg">
    <statement><p>Simplify the function formula, and if applicable, write the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ h(y) = {\frac{y+9}{y^{2}+14y+45}} }</m></p>
<p>Reduced <m>h(y)=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{1}{y+5}, y\ne -9</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cancel common factors.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   h(y) \amp = {\frac{y+9}{y^{2}+14y+45}} \\
                 \amp = \frac{{y+9}}{{\left(y+9\right)\mathopen{}\left(y+5\right)}} \\
                 \amp = {\frac{1}{y+5}, y\ne -9}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>y+9</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the reduction is <m>y \ne -9</m>.</p>
</solution>
